SIMPLE: thurl
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thurl
<hw>Thurl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧yrel</ets> a hole. ⟦root⟧53. See <er>Thirl</er>,
<er>Thrill</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A hole; an aperture.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A short
communication between adits in a mine.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A long
adit in a coalpit.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thurl</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Thurl
<hw>Thurl</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Thrill</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To cut through; to pierce.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mining)</fld> <def>To cut through, as a partition
between one working and another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thurling</ent>⟦br⟧
